 remains unproven.</div><div style=3D"margin: 0;" class=3D"revue-p">
<b>The conspiracy about Facebook targeting ads at you by snooping with your=
 phone=E2=80=99s microphone is now part of the congressional record</b>. Fo=
r years now, Facebook has struggled to contain <a href=3D"http://em.getrevu=
e.co/mpss/c/2AA/1EoYAA/t.2gj/55GiJaRhQvWuprF1_O3GKw/h6/5nR3kgrWOioxqOYwlsgm=
ouC9XUdaJEitpJt6IGCEI03ez8DtxzSci2qAyYEVBP2yj-2F7SsMQTn4VwIAZ-2FV8uhoQ-3D-3=
D" style=3D"color: #8b9dc3" target=3D"_blank">an urban legend</a> that the =
company=E2=80=99s ad targeting is so effective because the company listens =
to your conversations in real time through your phone=E2=80=99s microphone.=
 Thanks to Sen. Gary Peters (D-MI), <a href=3D"http://em.getrevue.co/mpss/c=
/2AA/1EoYAA/t.2gj/55GiJaRhQvWuprF1_O3GKw/h7/SZrPzbQR0Tj0WaBKLu6ypbI9duC2WdF=
